o Antill\u00f3n]]\t\n|KO\n|3 (12), {{small|2:39}}\n|[[Brandon R\u00edos vs. Urbano Antill\u00f3n|Jul 9, 2011]]\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Home Depot Center]], [[Carson, California]], U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Retained WBA lightweight title}}\n|-\n|28\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|27\u20130\u20131\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|VEN}} [[Miguel Acosta]]\n|TKO\n|10 (12), {{small|1:14}}\n|Feb 26, 2011\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Pearl Concert Theater, Paradise, Nevada, U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Won [[list of WBA world champions#Lightweight|WBA lightweight title]]}}\n|-\n|27\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|26\u20130\u20131\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Omri Lowther]]\n|TKO\n|5 (10), {{small|2:04}}\n|[[Manny Pacquiao vs. Antonio Margarito|Nov 13, 2010]]\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Cowboys Stadium]], [[Arlington, Texas]], U.S.}}\n|\n|-\n|26\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|25\u20130\u20131\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Anthony Peterson]]\n|{{abbr|DQ|Disqualification}}\n|7 (12), {{small|3:00}}\n|Sep 11, 2010\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Pearl Concert Theater]], Paradise, Nevada, U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Peterson disqualified for repeated low blows}}\n|-\n|25\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|24\u20130\u20131\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Jorge Teron]]\n|TKO\n|3 (10), {{small|1:13}}\n|Feb 6, 2010\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[McAllen Convention Center|Convention Center]], [[McAllen, Texas]], U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Won vacant [[North American Boxing Federation|NABF]] [[lightweight]] title}}\n|-\n|24\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|23\u20130\u20131\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} Lorenzo Estrada \n|TKO\n|1 (10), {{small|2:06}}\n|Nov 6, 2009\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Convention Center, [[Garden City, Kansas]], U.S.}}\n|\n|-\n|23\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|22